sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742139
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Zeaxanthin (yellow pigment) synthesis operon without PstI sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Zeaaxnthin, a yellow pigment, is synthesised from farnesyl disphosphate in five sequential enzymatic steps.
These five enzymes are encoded by the genes CrtE, CrtB, CrtI, CrtY and CrtZ.
More information on the zeaxanthin biosynthesis pathway may be found on the [http://parts.mit.edu/igem07/index.php/Edinburgh/Yoghurt/Design#Colour_Production Edinburgh Yoghurt Wiki]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
All five genes were isolated from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321)
More information about carotenoid synthesis may be found in these references:
Diversity of Carotenoid Synthesis Gene Clusters from Environmental Enterobacteriaceae Strains, N Sedkova, APPLIED AND ENVIRONMENTAL MICROBIOLOGY, 71(12): 8141???8146 (2005)
Elucidation of Pathway the Erwinia uredovora Carotenoid Biosynthetic by Functional Analysis of Gene Products Expressed in Escherichia coli, N Misawa, et al, JOURNAL OF BACTERIOLOGY, 172(12): 6704-6712 (1990)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Two PstI sites have been removed from CrtI gene via point mutation.
All five genes were cloned so they retain their native ribosome binding sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742116
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: crtE with native ribosome binding site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
CrtE encodes geranylgeranyl pyrophosphate synthase
Enzyme converts two farnesyl diphosphate molecules into geranylgeranyl diphosphate
Part of the carotenoid synthesis pathway
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Diversity of Carotenoid Synthesis Gene Clusters from Environmental Enterobacteriaceae Strains, N Sedkova, APPLIED AND ENVIRONMENTAL MICROBIOLOGY, 71(12): 8141???8146 (2005)
Elucidation of Pathway the Erwinia uredovora Carotenoid Biosynthetic by Functional Analysis of Gene Products Expressed in Escherichia coli, N Misawa, et al, JOURNAL OF BACTERIOLOGY, 172(12): 6704-6712 (1990)
Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Ensured gene contained ribosome binding site by designing primers to include the site

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742133
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CrtIB genes with PstI site mutated out
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
CrtIB encodes two enzymes, which make up steps three and two in the carotenoid biosynthesis pathway respectively.
CrtI encodes phytoene desaturase and CrtB encodes Phytoene synthase.
Both cloned genes still have their native ribosome binding sites.
More information about the carotenoid synthesis pathway may be found on the [http://parts.mit.edu/igem07/index.php/Edinburgh/Yoghurt/Design#Colour_Production Edinburgh Yoghurt Wiki]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Genes were both isolated from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080, ATCC 19321
Diversity of Carotenoid Synthesis Gene Clusters from Environmental Enterobacteriaceae Strains, N Sedkova, APPLIED AND ENVIRONMENTAL MICROBIOLOGY, 71(12): 8141???8146 (2005)
Elucidation of Pathway the Erwinia uredovora Carotenoid Biosynthetic by Functional Analysis of Gene Products Expressed in Escherichia coli, N Misawa, et al, JOURNAL OF BACTERIOLOGY, 172(12): 6704-6712 (1990)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The CrtI gene contained two PstI sites, which were both mutated out using point mutagenesis

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742117
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CrtY with native ribosome binding site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
CrtY encodes a lycopene cyclase
Converts lycopene to B-carotene
B-carotene is used as an orange pigment and is a vitamin A precursor

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742118
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CrtZ with native ribosome binding site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
crtZ encodes a beta-carotene hydroxylase
Converts B-carotene into zeaxanthin (yellow pigment)
Part of the carotenoid biosynthesis pathway
